The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Chris Gayle ruled out 
                                                                                                                                                                                           Chris Gayle ruled out 
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Chris Gayle has been ruled out of the first edition of the IPL with a groin injury, according to a spokesman for Kolkata Knight Riders.         
	He suffered the injury during West Indies home series against Sri Lanka.         
	However, he will be coming to the city in the first week of May to spend some time with the Knight Riders team.         
	There are no plans to get a replacement.         
	Ticket sales         
	Ticket sales for Kolkata Knight Riders next home match against Mumbai Indians on April 29 will begin from Thursday.                                                                                                                          
